" All system-wide defaults are set in $VIMRUNTIME/voidlinux.vim (usually
" just /usr/share/vim/vimfiles/voidlinux.vim) and sourced by the call
" to :runtime you can find below.
"
" If you wish to change any of those settings, you should do it in this
" file (/etc/vimrc), since voidlinux.vim will be overwritten every time
" an upgrade of the Vim packages is performed.

" It is recommended to make changes after sourcing voidlinux.vim since
" it alters the value of the 'compatible' option.
"
" Credit: https://www.archlinux.org/packages/extra/x86_64/vim/

" This line should not be removed as it ensures that various options
" are properly set to work with the Vim-related packages.
runtime! voidlinux.vim

" Uncomment for old-style vim functionalty:
"runtime! vimrc_example.vim

" Better yet, read the vim manual and configure Vim to your own liking.

" Uncomment to disable loading defaults if ~/.vimrc is missing:
"let skip_defaults_vim=1
